item.title: APAC keyless entry system market to decline at 0.5% CAGR by 2029: GlobalData
item.description: Keyless entry systems in vehicles include numerous security features designed to deter theft. However, as automotive technology evolves, so do the techniques and tools used by hackers. This has pressured manufacturers to focus on developing innovative solutions to combat theft.

item.title: Boeing Suspends 777X Flight Tests After Parts Connecting To Engine Fail
item.description: Boeing has suspended flight testing of its new 777X wide-body jet after identifying the failure of a part connecting the engine to the body of the aircraft, the latest in a long line of quality control issues for the troubled US aerospace giant.
